THE GAME
--------

  'Geodesik' is a Workbench game where you have to 'grow' crystals
toward the center of a geode-like structure, so they are all of
the same size. Crystals can be of 4 sizes: short, medium, tall and
tallest. As you grow one crystal, another crystal may randomly
increase or decrease in size...

  To make a crystal grow, click in the general area where it is
located, between the geode's center to the coloured edge at the
base of the crystal. When a crystal is at its tallest size, it
will stay that way, unless the game reduces its size...

  There are 4 types of geodes, each with a variable amount of
crystal stability; from a very high stability (which is obviously
easier to complete) to a very low stability, which will make you
'battle' for awhile with some pesky crystals...

  A 'Same size crystals' percentage indicator, displayed at the
right of the game board, shows the percentage of the highest
number of crystals that are of the same size. The game is
completed when that percentage reaches 100%.

  Complete the game in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

